XOOX Video Making Challenge
OFFICIAL RULES
1. NO PURCHASE NECESSARY TO ENTER OR WIN the XOOX Video
Making Challenge (the Challenge).
2. The Promotor
HOW TO ENTER: Beginning on March 11th, 2024 at 12:00:00 AM Pacific Standard
Time through August 8th 2024 at 11:59:59 PM Pacific Standard Time, log on to the
XOOX Pet App (the App) and click on the join button for the Challenge and
follow the on-screen entry instructions. Fill in all required information. You may
enter multiple times per pet; however, no more than one cash reward win per pet
is permitted. If one pet wins the multiple cash rewards, it will only receive the
highest ranked reward. Multiple submissions of videos may be uploaded to
increase the participant's likelihood of winning; however, in the event that the
participant secures victory in multiple submissions, only the submission with the
highest count of likes shall be considered for eligibility and reward. Use of any
robotic, automatic, programmed, or similar entry method or entering more than
the number of times permitted will void all entries and result in disqualification.
You may not enter more times than indicated by using multiple email addresses,
identities, or devices in an attempt to circumvent the rules.
3. ELIGIBILITY:
(a) Open to residents of the 50 United States and D.C., countries where
participation in the Challenge is legally permitted (ineligible countries include but not
limited to countries in the MENA region and China), 18 years of age and older as of
March 11th , 2024, except for employees of XOOX LAB ("Company"), their affiliates,
subsidiaries, agencies and those otherwise professionally connected to the Challenge
(collectively "Company-Affiliated Parties"), and members of their immediate family or
persons living in the same household. You must ensure that your XOOX LAB account
information is up to date and accurate. Void where prohibited.
(b) You may be required to present documentary proof of your eligibility
upon winning the Challenge. In the event that this proof is unable to be provided upon
request, the Company may disqualify you from the Challenge and/or withhold the prize.
4. CHALLENGE:
(a) The winner of the Challenge will be determined based on the number of
likes received by a photo or video uploaded by you during the term of the Challenge. The
Company selects the winner from among all eligible entries received. Odds of winning
depend on the number of entries received.
2
(b) The Company shall not be responsible for any entries which are lost,
damaged or delayed as a result of any postal failure, network, computer hardware or
software failure of any kind. Proof of sending cannot be proof of receipt. No applications
from agents, third parties, organized groups or applications automatically generated by
computer will be accepted.
(c) You shall confirm that your entry is entirely your own original work and
that any materials, information or intellectual properties used by you in creating your
entry do not and will not infringe the intellectual property, moral or other rights of any
third party. You shall ensure that any person(s) whose image or likeness has been used in
your entry has given their consent for the use of their image or likeness and has waived
any rights they may have in the images, videos or other media submitted. If such persons
are under the age of 18, you shall obtain their parental consent in writing.
(d) Your entry may be disqualified from the Challenge and you may lose any
prize if your entry contains any i) pornography, nudity or sexually explicit or vulgar
imagery, ii) abusive, offensive or hateful imagery or language, iii) harassing or
defamatory content, iv) content that compromises the privacy or safety of humans or
animals; v) content that demeans a particular gender, disability, religion, ethnicity or
nationality, (vi) violent or dangerous behavior, or (vii) spam, advertising or other
commercial activities, or any other type of content that is indecent, immoral,
discriminatory, offensive, or portrays or encourages illegal activities. Any entry that
contains such material will be disqualified.
(e) On submission, your entry and all materials created, developed or
produced by you in connection with your entry shall become the property of the
Company. You hereby assign to the Company all intellectual property rights (including
future rights and right to create derivative works and use the entry for promotional
purposes) in your entry and otherwise arising in connection with your entry. You also
waive all moral rights in relation to your entry to which you may now or at any future
time be entitled under statutes on copyrights, etc. from time to time in force anywhere in
the world. You agree to take all such action and sign all such documentation as may be
necessary to give effect to this Paragraph.
(f) Potential winners will be notified by email or phone and must sign and
return any required Affidavit of Eligibility and Release within [15] days of the date notice
is sent or such other date set by Company. Failure to respond within the applicable time
period will result in forfeiture of prize and Company shall have the option to award the
prize to an alternate winner. The return of any prize notification or prize as undeliverable
may result in disqualification and an alternate winner may be selected.
(g) All income taxes resulting from acceptance of prize are the responsibility
of winner. By entering this Challenge, entrant accepts and agrees to these Official Rules
and the decisions of the Company, which shall be final in all matters. Acceptance of a
prize also constitutes permission to the Company-Affiliated Parties to use winner's name,
likeness and biographical information for marketing purposes without further
3
compensation or right of approval, unless prohibited by law. All federal and state laws
apply.
(h) The decision of the Company shall be final and no correspondence or
discussion will be made. The Company reserves the right to withhold prizes if there is an
insufficient number of entries or entries of insufficient quality.
(i) Prizes are not transferable.
(j) The Company reserves the right to use its reasonable discretion and
disqualify you if your entry or conduct contravenes the spirit of these Rules or the
intention of the Challenge. The Company reserves the right to substitute a prize of equal
or greater value. If a potential winner is disqualified for any reason, the Company will
award the applicable prize to an alternate winner using the same method to find the
winner of the Challenge. Only two (2) alternate winners will be chosen, after which the
prize will remain un-awarded.
5. SUBMISSION GUIDELINES & DETERMINATION OF WINNERS:
(a) Submissions must:
(i) Create a video that's one minute (1 min) or less.
(ii) Must contain pets of any speicies (dog, cat, etc.)
(iii) Must be submitted through the XOOX app Challenge.
(b) The winner of the Challenge will be determined as follows:
(i) The videos will be evaluated based on:
(A) Total number of likes for the video - 50%
(B) Judges' votes (Judges will be selected by XOOX) - 50%
(ii) How the Judges Will Evaluate:
(A) Overall video quality
(B) Content creativity (original ideas, etc.)
(C) Effectiveness measure as the commercial film
(D) Must include pets in the video
